reviewText: Tight-lipped.  (Not a compliment.)  DO NOT BE FOOLED by the X rating, there is no explicit action here at all so thanks for the April Fool's joke on me.  Basically this is many scenes of girls who seem to have no idea how to make love to a woman.  The kissing lacks passion, the second base action looks tentative, and they avoid contact with the vag completely (all you see when they do pretend to go downtown is their huge hairdos, and they have no clue at all how to use their hands).  So as far as sapphic thrills, this dvd is total BS.The girls aren't unattractive though, and one scene toward the end with a nice threesome is not too bad, at least the nudity gets more explicit (yet still a lot of quick passes - the camera never seems to just stand still for a few seconds and let the girls show you something).  The girls throughout have an over-groomed appearance though, kinda fake with too much makeup, no blemishes, and not a lot of real breasts or interesting bush.  I think at this point Playboy is more erotic than this.  Pretty but pointless.This dvd even came with a funny little "extreme parental advisory" sticker on it, warning about sexual situations and nudity and whatnot.  WTF - parental advisory?  That right there suggested what I was about to watch was probably lame cable version pron.  And it is somewhat, but worse.  There are the same kind of frustrating edits, but in this dvd nothing's really happening anyway.  My first Peach purchase, and my last.
Title: Taste Like a Peach
